S6.description:
チャットで入れるオンライン作業部屋。

世界初のYoutubeライブ映像＆チャットを利用した完全自動型のオンライン入退室システム（人数無制限）（24時間）配信です。

自習室というタイトルではありますが、ここでは勉強以外のさまざまな作業（散歩，ヨガ，仮眠，瞑想，ゲーム，掃除など）もできます。

※スパム防止のため、チャンネル登録者のみモードになることがあります🙏そのときはチャンネル登録するとすぐに利用できます。

🔰【使い方】🔰
どなたでも今すぐ入室できます！
最初は次の2つのコマンドだけおぼえれば十分です。

・ルームに入って作業を始める
チャットに「!in」と書く。
作業内容もつけたい場合は「!in  作業内容」と書く。

・ルームを出る
チャットに「!out」と書く。

Botから返事があるまで待ってください。

コマンド一覧：https://kani3camp.github.io/youtube-study-space/docs/essential


🍉【作業名を書くには】🍉
・入室するときに「!in   国語」のように書く。
・すでに入室している場合は、「!change   国語」のように書く。

【作業名の規制に関して】
このオンライン作業部屋では、あえて自由度の高い作業名の表現を許容しています。そのため、勉強とは関係ない作業名が目に入ることがあります。ご了承ください。


🍫【主なコマンド】🍫
・!seat
今座っている座席番号と、入室からの経過時間、自動退室までの残り時間をBotが教えてくれます。

・!席番号
席を指定して入室できます。空いている座席を画面から探してください。
（例：「!32」で32番の席に入室）

・!more
作業時間を延長する。（例：「!more  100」で100分延長）

・!break
入室中に少し休憩する。基本15分、最大30分。

・!change
作業名や入室時間の変更をする。入室時間とは、入室してから自動退室までの時間。
（例：「!change  work  数学  min  70」で作業名を数学にして、入室時間を70分に変更する。例えば入室から30分経っていたら、自動退室まで40分が設定される。）

・!info
累計作業時間と、本日の累計作業時間をBotが教えてくれます。

・!report
⚠️緊急時以外使用しないでください！⚠️ 
管理人とモデレーターに連絡がいきます。スペースをあけて報告内容を書いてください。
例：「!report  荒らしがいます」「!report  100番席の作業名が不快です」
※管理人やモデレーターがすぐに来れないこともあります。
※質問や問い合わせは、!reportではなく概要欄にある問い合わせフォームから。

・チャットでの雑談は全然OKです

❓【Q&A】❓
詳細は https://youtube-study-space.notion.site/FAQ-494da77e1cd5489298500c66866f47bd

Q. 座席に座ると何が起こるのでしょう？
A. 入室するとライブ映像内に皆さんの名前や作業内容が表示されます。

Q. この自習室を使う意味って何ですか？
A. 現実の自習室や図書館に行かなくても、他の人と同じ時間・空間で勉強しているように感じることができます。また、他の人の作業内容を見て、「みんなこういうこと勉強してるんだな」「この人私と同じことやってるな」などと思えて、モチベーションがあがる人もいます。

Q. 入室時間の延長はどこまで出来ますか？
A. やろうと思えば無限にできます。例えば「!more  m=100」を100分ごとに書き続ければいいです。ただし、１つの座席に座れる時間の上限があるため、途中で強制で席移動することがあります。

Q. 自動退室って？
A. !outをし忘れることがあるので、自動退室の機能があります。自動退室までの時間は基本120分・最大360分です。入室時に指定したり、延長したりできます。

Q. 作業の累計時間はリセットできますか？
A. 累計作業時間をリセットする機能は今はありませんが、今後、週ごと・月ごとの累計作業時間をカウントする機能を追加しようと考えています。

Q. 席を書いても後にチャットした人に席が取られます
A. 遅延によってあなたにだけそう見えています😓コマンドは順番通りに処理されます。https://youtube-study-space.notion.site/d85d84bad3b24e6f8e88601f9e74df0a をご覧ください。

Q. 画面右下のタイマーの時間割ありますか？
A. https://youtube-study-space.notion.site/385f89e0e7d14be7906555e1971f9ed0

Q. これいつまで配信してますか？始まりと終わりは何時ですか？
A. 24時間365日やっています。ただ、たまにメンテナンスをしたり、配信トラブル・システムトラブルが起こって一時的に視聴できなくなることもあります。

Q. Youtubeの画面を閉じても大丈夫ですか？
A. 大丈夫です。配信を見るのをやめても退室させられることはありません。

Q. 作業せず入るだけの人が出てくると思うのですが、そこはどう考えていますか？
A. その通りで、真面目に使わない人は必ずいると思います。気にしないでください。ちなみに、累積作業時間に応じて席の色が変わるランク表示機能は、他人と比較するためではなく、自分の努力の積み重ねの指標として活用してほしいです。

Q. フードサービスは本物の食事ではないですか。本物でないなら機能の目的はなんですか
A. !orderによる注文は、あくまで仮想的なものです。このオンライン作業部屋自体が仮想的なもので、そのなかでできることを増やしています。現実ではないですが、作業のお供として活用される方もいると思います。

Hi!

🔥Key to success - """"BE CONSISTENT""""🔥

What are you studying and where are you joining from? I also wonder what type of videos you like, study at the library or study at home? Your opinions are quite important to me; and, if you let me know what type of videos you like to watch, I would be happy.

✧･ﾟ at the beginning of the study sessions, make sure to:
- turn off anything you're not going to be using to study
- have your materials ready to go
- have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
- have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)


✧･ﾟ during the breaks:
- stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
- make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
- refill anything that needs to get refilled
- talk to friends/update family

✧･ﾟ at the end of this video:
if you want to continue studying, give yourself a longer break and you can the next session video!

you're set to go! ♡

!top - Top Points

- Being nice and respectful is mandatory!
- Spamming, harassment, trolling, bullying, repeating and all capital messages are definitely prohibited!

To those who are starting :
In order to study or do anything for long periods of time you need a strong purpose and you must be willing to endure challenges. If I can do this, think about what you can accomplish. If you're starting out, start from low intervals(10-30 minutes) and gradually increase once you feel you're comfortable. If you feel like quitting, visualize your goals and evaluate your purpose. Learn to accept challenges in your life to become uncommon.

JUST DO IT!

안녕하세요! 법무사 시험을 준비하는 꾸준맨 부맨입니다.
이전에는 장교(ROTC 출신)로 해병대에 6년간 몸담았고, 전역 후 그간 배워보고 싶었던 영상 편집, 코딩, IT(네트워크, 정보보안 등) 여러가지를 공부 했습니다. 그러던 중 좋은 기회를 만나 쿠팡 자회사인 CFS에 입사. 물류센터에서 근무를 했습니다. 군인시절부터 조직(회사)에 의지 하지 않아도 되는 내 능력으로 내 삶을 살고 싶다는 생각을 자주 했고, 경제적으로 독립한 전문가(장인)가 되고 싶었습니다. 

군대 후배의 추천으로 법무사에 도전하게 되었고, 쿠팡 퇴사 후 2021년 8월 말부터 법무사 1차 공부를 시작해서, 1년 만에 집에서 인강으로 22년 법무사 1차 시험에 합격하였고, 당해 2차 시험은 130명 안에 들지 못했습니다. 23년에 2차 공부를 후회없이 하였지만 불합격했습니다. 새로운 마음으로 재동차 도전중입니다. 같이 힘내요🔥🔥🔥

22년 11월 2차 시험이 끝나고 공부가 잘 되지 않아, 2023년 새해를 맞아 스터디윗미를 해보자는 생각을 했고, 열심히 실행하고 있습니다. 항상 시작이 가장 어려운 것 같습니다. JUST DO IT!!!그래도 해보는게 중요하다고 생각합니다.

미라클 모닝, 미라클 러닝, 공부, 독서 등 스스로 동기부여하려고 노력하고 있고, 가지고 있는 좋은 에너지들을 많은 분들과 주고 받고 싶어요! 부지러너 여러분들과 같이 2024년 목표 달성 해요! 들어와서 봐주시는 분들 정말 감사합니다!

I do a real-time study with me live every day except for one day of the week. I want to motivate you as a friend who studies with you. Even though time is different, we have the same heart to strive for our dreams.

This 24/7 stream from Studyistic is designed to motivate students anywhere, anytime! The study sessions are broadcast live, this makes it possible to study together at the same time with students from all over the world! You might even meet someone who studies the same as you but is 3000 km away from you. How 🆒 isn't this? Feel free to post a message in the chat and in no time you will have a whole group of study friends with you!😍

📌📌HOW TO USE THIS STREAM?
📖During the study sessions (always 50 minutes), study as hard as you can!🫡 
📢Then in the 10-minute break there is room for relaxation. During the break, there are many students who tell in the chat how their session was, what the plans are for the next session, or just something fun they want to share. Sharing with others in the chat what the plans are for the other sessions can be extra motivating. 

📌📌CHAT COMMANDS
🔆!weather city ⇾ Check the weather in your city.
🔆!quote ⇾ get a motivational quote in the chat.
🔆!welcome ⇾ For new subscribers/study buddies.
🔆!hug ⇾ Get a virtual hug.
🔆!instagram ⇾ Follow me on Instagram.

S41.title: 50대 감정평가사 도전기! 12HR-STUDY WITH ME (스터디 윗미)/공무원 시험/수험생/전문직 시험/혼자 공부/캠스터디/Huntington Beach/채팅은 쉬는시간에~ 2025-05-17 10:16
S41.description:
50대에 접어들게 되면서....
감히 감정평가사라는 정말 어려운 시험에 도전하게 되었습니다.
서울대, 연고대 출신 합격생이 가장 많고, 
8천여명중에 150~200여명 안팎의 인원만 합격하는 극악의 난이도의 시험입니다.
50대는 1년에 보통 전국에서 2~3명 내외로 합격하더군요....
그런 똑똑하고 체력좋은 젊은 20대~30대 친구들한테 제가 무모한 싸움을 걸었네요.
몸과 머리가 젊을때 같지않지만, 절실함 하나만을 가지고 시작했습니다!
유튜브 공부법은 약하디 약한 저의 의지를 바로 잡는데 꼭 필요한 장치인것 같습니다.
매일매일 이해하지 못하고 암기하지 못함에서 오는 
'불합격하면 어떡하지??'라는 극악의 불안감이 엄습해오지만...
꼭 이겨내겠습니다!
올해 4월 1차, 내년 7월 2차 시험 합격을 목표로 달려가고 있습니다.
저를 아시던 모르시던 한번씩 들어오셔서
*구독, 좋아요 눌러주시고*
[공부 잘하고 있는지 확인해 주시고] 
[만약 나약한 모습을 보인다면 쓴소리해주세요] 
부탁드립니다!!
마지막으로, 
여기 들어 오시는 모든 분들이 준비하시는 시험에 꼭 합격하시길 기원드립니다.
감사합니다!!

As I entered my 50s...
I dare to take a very difficult exam called a certified public appraiser.
It's an extremely difficult exam that only about 150~200 out of 8,000 passed every year in Korea.
Usually, only two or three people in their 50s pass the test a year...
I started a reckless fight against those smart, energetic young people in their 20s and 30s.
My body and head aren't like when I was young, but I started with only one desperation!
The YouTube study method seems to be a necessary device to strengthen my weak will.
Everyday i'm worried that I might fail the exam, but I'll overcome it!
I am studying hard with the goal of passing the first test in April this year. 
and the second exam (Final) in July next year.
Whether you know me or not, please come in.
*Please press subscribe and like*
And please check if I am studying well.
If I don't study or show a weak mental state, please say something bitter.
Please!
Lastly, I hope this real-time streaming will be of great help to your studies.
Thank you!!

Hi ^^ We’re Anne🐷 & Adrien🐭!
We’re a couple who met during our university years. We’ve always supported and motivated each other to study and work hard to reach our shared goal: getting into medical school. And this year, we finally made it! We are now in our first year of medical school.

Through our YouTube channel, we want to connect with new people, share our journey in higher education, motivate others to study—and even motivate ourselves. We know how hard it can be to sit down and get to work.
Sometimes you feel like it’s already too late to start. Or you avoid trying just so you can blame your failure on not working enough—telling yourself it’s not because you’re not smart, just that you didn’t try. Or maybe you’re scared it will be too hard, so you don’t even want to begin.

But we need to stop being afraid of failure. Everyone  ail at something at some point. What really matters is learning from your mistakes and trying again.
The real failure is choosing to stay down instead of getting back up.

🧠 Tips to Stay Focused

1. Start small
If you struggle to focus for more than 5 minutes, start with just 5. That’s already better than zero! Usually, the hardest part is just starting. So tell yourself you’ll work for 5 minutes—you might end up doing more, and if not, that’s totally okay. Start with 5 minutes of work and 10 minutes of break. Then increase slowly each day until you find the rhythm that works for you.

2. Set realistic goals
Plan your day with goals that are actually achievable. That feeling of success will motivate you to keep going—and maybe even push you to do a bit more. But always remember to keep it realistic. Feeling like you’ve failed can be very discouraging.

3. Talk to people during your breaks
Taking time to chat helps release pressure and puts things into perspective—like fears about falling behind or not being fast enough.

🌙 minimal chatting while the study session is going on.
🌙 be respectful and kind.
🌙 no spamming, advertising and inappropriate behaviour.

Commands:
⭐ !quote - motivational quotes
⭐ !genie - start counting your study time. If u just joined, type !genie. No time will be added yet. When the break starts, type !genie again to add 1 hour. If it fails, type !genie again after 10 mins. If Streamlabs still isn't counting properly, notify our mods and they will manually add the hour for u. Otherwise, please avoid chatting outside of break ^-^ 
⭐ !remove - to remove an hour from your total study time.
⭐ !target (task) - to add a task to your to-do list.
⭐ !done (task) - when you finish your task.
⭐ !forest (code) (duration) (tree name) - to share your forest code.
⭐ !foresthelp - to get more commands for Forest's FAQ

S72.description:
Welcome to my “Study With Me” 2-hour live study session! Whether you’re preparing for an exam, working on an assignment, or just trying to stay productive, this video is designed to help you stay focused, motivated, and accountable. Join me as I study live for 2 hours straight, no distractions, just pure study time — and feel like you’re studying with a friend, right from the comfort of your home!

This is a real-time study session (recorded live) where we study together for 2 hours continuously. It’s perfect for those who enjoy the Pomodoro technique, body doubling, or need a virtual study buddy to stay on track. Whether you’re a student preparing for your school, college, university exams, competitive exams like NEET, JEE, UPSC, SAT, GRE, GMAT, or simply working on a personal project, this video will give you the environment you need to stay committed.

In this video:
✅ 2 hours of live study
✅ Minimal talking for maximum focus
✅ Realistic study atmosphere: no music, no distractions, just natural sounds
✅ Perfect for “study with me” fans, deep work sessions, and productivity seekers

WHY WATCH THIS STUDY WITH ME VIDEO?

I created this study with me live stream to help fellow students stay motivated and create a sense of companionship even while studying alone. Sometimes we all need someone by our side, even virtually, to keep going. This video can help boost your productivity, especially if you’re struggling with procrastination or want a structured block of study time.

Feel free to pause, replay, or study alongside me in real-time. You can even use this as a timer or background video while you tackle your own work.

⬇️🟢stream schedule, links and faq down below!!🟢⬇️
this channel isn’t just for studying; 

I've been there; I almost killed myself at a railway and stopped studying for half a year, it would be easy to just give up and let life win, but instead I use my situation to drive myself forward even when i dont fucking feel like it.

It can get overwhelming sometimes, especially if like me you have no one to talk to, but if you and me are studying together we've got eachother. Lets get through this together :)

mental health stuff:
due to severe mental health issues I don't talk during my streams in the breaks, its because I go through a lot of shit in my life and I dont want to ruin other people's days by putting negative energy out there. Instead I try to record videos as much as I can where I'm just talking about life stuff, hopefully these videos resonate with some of yall, and I'm sorry I can't talk during the stream I promise it will get better.

🧉 Hello student, how are you? It's great to have you here!
I just wanted to let you know that this study livestream is live 24 hours a day, every day of the week, so that whenever you feel like studying, you can rely on a platform that motivates you and enables you to achieve that goal. And if you ever feel like appearing on the livestream, join us on this Discord link: [https://discord.gg/K5kcaMSJaU]

But before we begin, if possible, please leave a like on the video, subscribe to the channel, and share your study objectives in the comments!
Finally, grab your water, matecito, coffee, or tea to stay hydrated during your study sessions.

🍅 Pomodoro Technique:
We will be using the Pomodoro technique, which consists of four 50-minute study sessions, interspersed with 10-minute breaks. The purpose of this technique is to maintain focus for 50 minutes through conditioning. In the beginning, it might be difficult, so try starting with cycles of 15-25 minutes. However, with persistence, you can achieve the desired results!

⭐ A little bit about me and why I created this channel:
My name is Arthur, I'm 24 years old, and I'm a third-year medical student at UBA College. I created this channel to help myself maintain discipline and focus in my studies, and if possible, to also help other students do the same.
